[Student "S"]
{When WEST gives immediate \S support, EAST's thoughts naturally 
turn to slam. This is a good hand to use Blackwood on, so EAST bids 4NT.

WEST's 5\D answer shows one Ace, which EAST cleverly deduces 
must be the \CA.

EAST bids 6\S since WEST has not bid strongly enough to think about 7.}

