{EAST's jump to 4\C is a Splinter bid, at least 4-card \H support, 
at least opening hand, and a \C Singleton or Void.

WEST bids 4NT, Blackwood.

EAST's 5NT reply shows two Aces and a Void somewhere, obviously \Cs.

WEST counts thirteen tricks and bids 7\H.}

